explanation:
Given, $S=\dfrac{\sqrt{a b}}{c^{3} d^{4}}$<br>Percentage error in $S$ is given as,<br>$\frac{{\Delta S}}{S} \times 100 = \left[ {\begin{array}{*{20}{l}}
  \begin{gathered}
  \frac{1}{2} \times \frac{{\Delta a}}{a} \times 100 + \frac{1}{2} \hfill \\
   \times \frac{{\Delta b}}{b} \times 100 + 3 \times \frac{{\Delta c}}{c} \hfill \\ 
\end{gathered}  \\ 
  { \times 100 + 4 \times \frac{{\Delta d}}{d} \times 100} 
\end{array}} \right]$<br>$=\dfrac{1}{2} \times 2 \%+\dfrac{1}{2} \times 1 \%+3 \times 1 \%+4 \times 1 \%$<br>$=1 \%+\dfrac{1}{2} \%+3 \%+4 \%=8.5 \%$<br>Which is nearest to $9 \%$.<br>So, the correct option is (3).
